
[1]tremendous

   TREMEN'DOUS, a. [L. tremendus, from tremo, to tremble.]

   1. Such as may excite fear or terror; terrible; dreadful. Hence,

   2. Violent; such as may astonish by its force and violence; as a
   tremendous wind; a tremendous shower; a tremendous shock or fall; a
   tremendous noise.
